name: Purple Flowers of Barberton
description: Shooting macro is a great way to spend the time in the middle of the day when the light is not ideal for other photos. It also works great on overcast days or just after it has rained when the light is lovely and soft. These were flowers in the rock garden on my farm after a thunderstorm. I am always fascinated by the shallow depth of field that I can play with flowers like these.
